RUSTENBURG A bottle store was looted and pupils removed from schools in Coligny during a protest on Monday, North West police said. The protest is apparently linked to an incident in which a child, suspected to be 12 years old, alighted from a moving vehicle on Thursday. He was seriously injured and later died at the hospital. WATCH: Anti-Zuma protests spread to LondonHe said protesting community members allegedly took pupils out of classes to join them in the protest. Public order police are managing the situation. No reports of injuries have been received, he said.African News Agency